ds: Accuracy of light-level loggers (geolocators) in forest habitats  Banding of migrant thrushes in Almirante, Panama  Seasonal variation in stopover site use:  Catharus  thrushes and vireos in northern Colombia  Geographic origins and timing of fall migration of the Veery in northern Colombia  Veery (  Catharus fuscescens  ), wintering locations, migratory connectivity, and a revision of its winter range using geolocator technology  Adaptations to migration in birds: Behavioural strategies, morphology and scaling effects  Field estimates of body drag coefficient on the basis of dives in passerine birds  Linking hydrogen (&delta;2H) isotopes in feathers and precipitation: Sources of variance and consequences for assignment to isoscapes  A multi-isotope (&delta; 13 C, &delta; 15 N, &delta; 2 H) feather isoscape to assign Afrotropical migrant birds to origins  Trends in trappability and stop-over duration can confound interpretations of population trajectories from long-term migration ringing studies  Long-distance bird migration within South America revealed by light-level geolocators  Model selection in ecology and evolution  A new multi-category classification of subcutaneous fat deposits of songbirds  Integrating information from geolocators, weather radar, and citizen science to uncover a key stopover area of an aerial insectivore  Modeling survival and testing biological hypotheses using marked animals: Case studies and recent advances  Returns and recoveries of banded North American birds in Panama and the tropics  Gray-cheeked Thrush (  Catharus minimus  )  Swainson's Thrush (  Catharus ustulatus  )  The influence of climate on the timing and rate of spring bird migration  New discoveries in landbird migration using geolocators, and a flight plan for the future  Stop early to travel fast: Modelling risk-averse scheduling among nocturnally migrating birds  Non-destructive techniques to assess body composition of birds: A review and validation study  Multiple-d